parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause unexpected shifting, loss of acceleration, and potentially lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Vibration or bumping sensation from the rear of the vehicle

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Remote starter malfunction can cause the vehicle to start without a key in the ignition, potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Vehicle starts without key in ignition
such as rolling out of a driveway.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Traction control malfunction can cause the vehicle to suddenly lose power or engage the brakes, potentially leading to accidents or loss of control.
Unintended acceleration can cause the vehicle to suddenly and unexpectedly accelerate, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates rapidly without pressing the accelerator pedal
the vehicle accelerates while in park or neutral gear
the vehicle fails to slow down when applying the brakes
the accelerator pedal sticks or feels stuck
the vehicle hesitates or lags when applying the accelerator pedal.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the idle speed control valve can cause the engine to rev to high RPM, leading to unintended acceleration and potential loss of control.
symptoms: The engine RPM increases rapidly without pressing the accelerator pedal
the vehicle accelerates while in park or neutral gear
the idle speed control valve is not functioning properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A sticking accelerator pedal can cause the vehicle to accelerate unexpectedly, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The accelerator pedal feels stuck or sticky
the vehicle accelerates rapidly without pressing the accelerator pedal
the accelerator pedal does not return to its normal position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden acceleration and brake failure can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially life-threatening situations.
symptoms: brake pedal going to the floor

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Spongy Brake Pedal and Failure to Stop
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The spongy brake pedal and failure to stop can cause accidents, injuries, and damage to vehicles and property.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Lockup and Loss of Steering Control
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The brake lockup and loss of steering control can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially life-threatening situations.
Tire sidewall failure can lead to a loss of tire pressure, causing the vehicle to lose control, which can result in accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Blisters or bubbles on the tire sidewall
repeated tire failures on the same side of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of airbags to deploy in the event of a crash can lead to serious injuries or fatalities, as the driver and passengers may be subjected to unrestrained forces and impacts.
symptoms: Airbags fail to deploy in a crash
often accompanied by bruising or trauma from the steering wheel or other interior components.
